{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01CAUPHnrwoCDPkmpeGUCUBK","type":"tool_result","content":"69-                       .cloche/<name>.cloche file in the project.\n70-  --prompt \"...\"       Prompt text passed to agent steps. Also available as\n71-  -p \"...\"             the short form.\n72:  --title \"...\"        Human-readable title for the run (shown in status/list).\n73-  --issue ID, -i ID    Associate a task/issue ID with the run (shown in list).\n74-  --keep-container     Do not remove the container after the run completes.\n75-                       Useful for debugging.\n76-\n77:The command prints the run ID on success. Use that ID with status, logs,\n78-poll, and stop.\n79-\n80-Examples:\n--\n114-  cloche resume develop-lush-fern-470c implement\n115-`,\n116-\n117:\t\"status\": `cloche status — Check run or daemon status\n118-\n119-With a run ID, shows the current state of a workflow run including its\n120-type, active step, and the result of each completed step.\n121-\n122:Without a run ID, shows a daemon status overview: version, run statistics,\n123-and active runs. In a project directory, also shows project name,\n124-concurrency, and orchestration loop state. Use --all to show global stats\n125-instead of project-specific stats.\n126-\n127-Usage:\n128:  cloche status [<run-id>] [--all]\n129-\n130-Arguments:\n131-  <run-id>    The run identifier returned by \"cloche run\" (optional).\n--\n147-Output (without run ID):\n148-  Daemon version\n149-  Project name and concurrency (if in project directory)\n150:  Orchestration loop status\n151-  Successful / total runs in the past hour\n152-  Active run count with per-run duration\n153-\n154-Examples:\n155:  cloche status abc123\n156:  cloche status\n157:  cloche status --all\n158-`,\n159-\n160-\t\"logs\": `cloche logs — Show logs for a run\n--\n195-(succeeded, failed, or cancelled).\n196-\n197-With a single run ID, prints step-level progress (same as before).\n198:With multiple run IDs, displays a compact status summary.\n199-\n200-Usage:\n201-  cloche poll <run-id> [run-id...]\n--\n535-Workflow Runs:\n536-  run        Launch a workflow run in a container\n537-  resume     Resume a failed workflow run from a specific step\n538:  status     Show daemon overview or check a specific run's status\n539-  logs       Show or stream logs for a run\n540-  poll       Wait for one or more runs to finish (blocks until terminal)\n541-  list       List runs for current project (or all projects)\n--\n562-Examples:\n563-  cloche init\n564-  cloche run --workflow develop --prompt \"Add user authentication\"\n565:  cloche status abc123\n566-  cloche logs abc123 --follow\n567-  cloche list\n568-  cloche loop --max 2"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"47e40bd9-5964-433f-ab2e-05da15c89f12","uuid":"e62a6b01-3a22-4e2d-bf9f-b9df3b4f4ede","timestamp":"2026-03-18T15:40:54.458Z","tool_use_result":{"mode":"content","numFiles":0,"filenames":[],"content":"69-                       .cloche/<name>.cloche file in the project.\n70-  --prompt \"...\"       Prompt text passed to agent steps. Also available as\n71-  -p \"...\"             the short form.\n72:  --title \"...\"        Human-readable title for the run (shown in status/list).\n73-  --issue ID, -i ID    Associate a task/issue ID with the run (shown in list).\n74-  --keep-container     Do not remove the container after the run completes.\n75-                       Useful for debugging.\n76-\n77:The command prints the run ID on success. Use that ID with status, logs,\n78-poll, and stop.\n79-\n80-Examples:\n--\n114-  cloche resume develop-lush-fern-470c implement\n115-`,\n116-\n117:\t\"status\": `cloche status — Check run or daemon status\n118-\n119-With a run ID, shows the current state of a workflow run including its\n120-type, active step, and the result of each completed step.\n121-\n122:Without a run ID, shows a daemon status overview: version, run statistics,\n123-and active runs. In a project 